<title>USA: Borg-Warner opens office for venture.</title>
<headline>Borg-Warner opens office for venture.</headline>
<dateline>CHICAGO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Borg-Warner Automotive Inc said Tuesday it opened a new engineering and sales office for its Japanese-based joint venture company, NSK-Warner KK, in Bloomfield Hills, Mich.</p>
<p>The new office, operating as NSK-Warner U.S.A. Inc, will provide support for U.S. transplant activities for Japanese automakers. Atsushi Sanada will serve as its president.</p>
<p>NSK-Warner, a joint venture between a subsidiary of Borg-Warner Automotive and NSK Ltd, was formed in 1964 to manufacture automatic transmission components for the Japanese automotive industry.</p>
<p>		((Reuters Chicago Newsdesk (312) 408-8787))</p>
